The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a framework for domain adaptation using unsupervised image-image translation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves supervised learning methods and generative adversarial networks, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions large-scale datasets, which suggests that it may be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
